Git Commit Rules
feat: Develop new features e.g. feat: add deposit feature
fix: Fix bugs e.g. fix: fix error
refactor: Optimize existing code e.g. refactor: optimize xxx
docs: Update project documentation e.g. docs: update README
style: Code style/linting rules e.g. style: add ESLint no-space rules
test: Add or modify test-related code e.g. test: add Deposit E2E test

1. check the staged changes.
2. check the actual changes in these files to understand what was modified.
3. generate the commit message by the rules above